summary: The document is a memorandum from the Central Cover Staff (CCS) in response to a request from the House Select Committee on Assassinations (HSCA) under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992. It details that the CCS files contain information on Marie L. PRISBRCK, a U.S. citizen and Agency contract agent from 1956 until her retirement in 1975, as documented in approximately 60 files. The memorandum clarifies that there is no information available on other individuals listed by the HSCA.
key_findings: The document is part of the records released under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
It responds to a request from the House Select Committee on Assassinations (HSCA) regarding specific individuals.
Information is available only on Marie L. PRISBRCK, a former Agency contract agent, with no data on others mentioned by the HSCA.
